<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-10-09T20:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-10-09T20:34:00-05:00" n="676" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">320/10–953: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United
                            Nations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lodge</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi></seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-10-09T20:34:00-05:00">October 9,
                                1953—8:34 p.m.</date></dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 96. Subject: Japanese associate
                        membership. <persName corresp="#p_SAWADAR1">Sawada</persName> advised
                            <persName corresp="#p_KEYDMK1">Key</persName> that his government had
                        decided not to apply for an associate membership and to hold this matter in
                        abeyance for the remainder of the current session inasmuch as discussion of
                        the membership question in the <hi rend="italic">ad hoc</hi> committee was
                        nearing its end. His government would, however, re-examine the question
                        prior to the opening of the ninth session in the light of international
                        conditions then existing.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lodge</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>